# Odisha Livestock & Poultry Analytics Dashboard

## Project Overview
This project analyzes district-wise livestock and poultry distribution across Odisha using SQL, MySQL, and Power BI. The dataset was stored in a MySQL database, queried using SQL, and visualized through an interactive Power BI dashboard.

## Objectives
- Understand SQL database creation and management
- Practice data querying and integration with Power BI
- Build interactive analytical dashboards
- Explore livestock and poultry distribution trends across Odisha districts

## Tools & Technologies
- MySQL
- SQL
- Power BI
- Power Query

## Features
- District-wise livestock analysis
- Poultry population comparison
- Interactive filters and slicers
- KPI cards for total livestock and poultry
- Comparative visualizations using bar and column charts

## Key Insights
- Mayurbhanj district showed the highest livestock and poultry population.
- Coastal and northern districts displayed higher poultry concentration.
- Significant variation exists between districts in livestock distribution.

## Skills Demonstrated
- Database management
- SQL querying
- Data cleaning and transformation
- Data visualization
- Dashboard design
- Business intelligence workflow

## Workflow
Excel Dataset → MySQL Database → SQL Queries → Power BI Dashboard

## Future Improvements
- Add yearly trend analysis
- Include GIS-based district mapping
- Integrate real-time agriculture datasets
- Add predictive analytics using Python/R

